Answer: a) Heap sort.

Explanation: Heap sort is an improvement to binary tree sort in that it allows for elements to be sorted in a more efficient manner. In Heap sort, the algorithm creates a max-heap from the partially sorted array and then recursively sorts the elements in the heap. This approach has a best-case time complexity of O(n log n) and a worst-case time complexity of O(n^2), compared to O(n^2) for binary tree sort.
